                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7332</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Hostetter</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 18, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Telegraph what, if anything, can be done, through friendly Indians or otherwise,
                    to obtain release of Mrs. John Lehr and children, still held prisoners by Yaquis
                    in Bacatete Hills.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
